transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Hello?

Speaker 1: Hello. How are we doing, sir?

Speaker 2: Okay, I'm just replying to the email that said,

Speaker 1: I didn't want to cancel my entire subscription.

Speaker 2: I think I ordered it twice.

Speaker 1: You want to cancel one of the orders?

Speaker 2: Yes, the second one.

Speaker 1: Which one is the second?

Speaker 2: What was the quantity for the second one?

Speaker 1: Ten.

Speaker 2: You want to cancel the ten?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I have 40 coming.

Speaker 2: I just wanted to change the amount.

Speaker 1: I don't need 40 pills a month.

Speaker 2: Yeah, no, no, you don't have to get it every month.

Speaker 1: I'm going to take care of that for you.

Speaker 2: I can pause the prescription and you can order as needed.

Speaker 1: But anyway, they're not going to send you 40 pills.

Speaker 2: It's not legal. It's impossible.

Speaker 1: Usually it's three months.

Speaker 2: They send you after three months 40 pills, not every month.

Speaker 1: Well, it said every 30 days.

Speaker 2: No, that's for the ten.

Speaker 1: You're not going to get 40.

Speaker 2: We cannot send you 40 pills every month.

Speaker 1: The pharmacy is not going to allow that.

Speaker 2: Okay, that's for us.

Speaker 1: That's why I'm going to try to change it.

Speaker 2: I tried to change it and then it looked like I had two orders.

Speaker 1: Well, I don't need that many.

Speaker 2: Ten a month is plenty.

Speaker 1: Okay, so which one do you want to keep?

Speaker 2: I'll keep the 40.

Speaker 1: That's fine for the first one.

Speaker 2: But what I ship here, the ten I ship before the 40 from what I can see.

Speaker 1: So the ten will be coming before?

Speaker 2: Cancel the 40 then.

Speaker 1: Okay, all right.

Speaker 2: Let me do that.

Speaker 1: And then how often do you want to have your ten pills sent?

Speaker 2: Every month, two months, three months, four months?

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's fine.

Speaker 2: I mean, which way is it cheaper?

Speaker 1: I'm trying to get it as cheap as I can get it.

Speaker 2: I mean, you can get it every two months.

Speaker 1: You can get it every month.

Speaker 2: Do you think ten pills every month is okay?

Speaker 1: I don't need ten pills every month, no.

Speaker 2: Ten pills every two months?

Speaker 1: That's fine?

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's fine.

Speaker 1: Okay, deal.

Speaker 2: We're pretty easy, Mr. Bowser.

Speaker 1: Yeah, ten pills every two months is fine.

Speaker 2: Yeah, whatever is your frequency, you just let us know.

Speaker 1: We move stuff around that you like in your account, okay?

Speaker 2: We just give us a ring, and we handle business together, okay?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: I canceled the 40 because apparently the ten pills were shipped already,

Speaker 1: but the 40 was still at the pharmacy.

Speaker 2: So I was able to cancel that with your refund, okay?

Speaker 1: And, yeah, I'll put you on a frequency of two months,

Speaker 2: so next refill will be in March, okay?

Speaker 1: Yeah, so everything looks great.

Speaker 2: Okay, so you canceled the 40.

Speaker 1: I'm getting the ten.

Speaker 2: How soon should I expect those?

Speaker 1: Okay, you have a tracking number in your e-mail.

Speaker 2: Let me click on that, and I'll tell you if there is a date already available.

Speaker 1: No, so they just created it, so you don't have a date yet,

Speaker 2: but you will receive the date.

Speaker 1: Your e-mail, gbowser71 at gmail.com.

Speaker 2: You have access to that e-mail?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, you will receive a tracking number.

Speaker 1: Usually it takes two to five business days, so today is Monday.

Speaker 2: The shipping level was created, so you could receive it by the end of the week.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, so you're all set so far.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome. You have a good one.

Speaker 1: Thank you. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
